      <p>
        <m>{\color{green} \text{To represent a compound inequality on a number line, illustrate the regions that satisfy each inequality and highlight the overlapping section.}}</m>
      </p>

      <example>

        <statement>

          <p>
            Illustrate the compound inequality <m>8 \le x \le 12</m> on a number line.
          </p>

        </statement>

        <solution>

          <p>
            The compound inequality <m>8 \le x \le 12</m> can be split into two simple inequalities: <m>x \ge 8</m> and <m>x \le 12</m>, draw closed points and then shade the region between them..
          </p>

          <image>
            <shortdescription>Number line</shortdescription>
            <latex-image>
              \begin{tikzpicture}
                % Draw number line with tick marks
                \draw[thick, ->] (5,0) -- (14.5,0);
                
                % Draw tick marks on the number line
                \foreach \x in {6,7,8,9,10,11,12,13,14} {
                    \draw[thick] (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1);
                }
                
                % Draw closed circles on x=8 and x=12
                \filldraw (8,0) circle (5pt);
                \filldraw (12,0) circle (5pt);
                
                % Draw shaded region between 8 and 12 on the number line
                \draw[thick] (8,0) -- (12,0);
                \fill[black, opacity=0.7] (8,-0.05) rectangle (12,0.1);
                
                % Label points
                \foreach \x in {6,7,8,9,10,11,12,13,14} {
                    \node[below] at (\x,0) {\x};
                }
                
              \end{tikzpicture}

            </latex-image>
          </image>

        </solution>

      </example>

